{"title":"10 winter training mistakes (and how to avoid them)","link":"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/winter-training-mistakes/","date":1612357200000,"content":"<img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=45&#038;resize=620,413\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1920,1278 1920w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1440,959 1440w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1200,799 1200w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960,639 960w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=720,479 720w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=576,383 576w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=360,239 360w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/Winter_training_4_flag-0a97cb7.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=180,119 180w, \" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" class=\"wp-image-414018 alignnone size-landscape_thumbnail\" alt=\"Winter training\" title=\"Winter training\" />                                            <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">If you’re looking to get the most out of your winter training, then you’re already going to be head and shoulders above those cyclists who go into hibernation come autumn, only to return once the temperature is back in double digits.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">That head start gives you the opportunity to put the building blocks in place for next year, whether building your fitness with long <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/base-training-cycling/\">base training</a> rides, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">putting together a </span><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/how-to-plan-your-winter-training/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">winter training plan</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, or </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">making the most of the </span><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/indoor-cycling-benefits/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">benefits of indoor cycling.</span></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Winter can be a tough time to be a cyclist — and that’s just the challenging conditions on the roads and trails – but that doesn’t mean you should give up. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Here are 10 training mistakes to avoid – and how you can overcome them.</span></p>\n<h2><span class=\"listicle__count\">Not having the right kit</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">First thing’s first, having the right kit is essential to surviving winter on the bike. While your bravery is admired if you’re still riding in a pair of <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-cycling-shorts/\">bib shorts</a> and a short-sleeve <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-cycling-jerseys/\">cycling jersey</a> in winter, at best you’re going to get cold, at worst you may pick up an illness or get hypothermia.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A pair of </span><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/best-winter-bib-tights-for-cycling/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">bib tights</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> should be a wardrobe staple come this time of year to keep the worst of the cold weather off your legs, while your top-half choice will depend on the conditions – from a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-autumn-cycling-clothing/\">long-sleeve jersey</a> on milder days through to a windproof and </span><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-waterproof-jackets-for-cyclists/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">waterproof jacket</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for when things get really bad.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Covering your hands and feet with </span><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-cycling-gloves-for-winter-riding/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">winter gloves</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-overshoes/\">overshoes</a> respectively will also keep your extremities warm, while a cap will keep the chill off your head.</span></p>\n<div class=\"image-handler__container image-handler__container--aspect\" style=\"padding-bottom: calc(100% / 1.501210653753);\">\n    <picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/CP-005-17-01-18-Robert-Smith-2018_preview-a8cb206-e1575392915182.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=298%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/CP-005-17-01-18-Robert-Smith-2018_preview-a8cb206-e1575392915182.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=598%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/CP-005-17-01-18-Robert-Smith-2018_preview-a8cb206-e1575392915182.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=897%2C599 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/CP-005-17-01-18-Robert-Smith-2018_preview-a8cb206-e1575392915182.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1197%2C799 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/